    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "DATE: May 26, 1949",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "BACKGROUND:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "Walter Winchell forwarded to the Director a Western Union",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "telegram he had received from Robert Ripley which stated that he, Ripley,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "had the only authentic Japanese flying saucer ever recovered in this",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "country. Mr. Winchell noted on the telegram, \"To J. Edgar Hoover - True?\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "DETAILS:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "This matter was discussed by Special Agent [REDACTED] with the Intelligence",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "Division of the Army, who advised that they had no information concerning any b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Japanese flying saucer ever having been recovered in the United States.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "This matter was discussed with Colonel [REDACTED], OSI-USAF,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "who advised on April 27, 1949 that he had interested himself in the flying saucers",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "and related subjects and that in so far as could be determined by him through his b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "sources in the Air Force, which are excellent, there is no authentic information",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "available concerning the phenomenon of the flying saucers. He advised he would check",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "with the authorities at Wright Field to determine if any information is available",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "concerning the recovery of a Japanese flying saucer.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "Colonel [REDACTED] has now advised that there is no information available",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "in any arm of the Air Force to the effect that any flying saucers of any kind have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "been recovered in the United States. Colonel [REDACTED] stated delay had been b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "encountered in determining this fact inasmuch as inquiries had been directed through",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "individuals known to him and trusted by him and not through the usual channels",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "from which he possibly would receive a stock answer.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "The details of this case were not discussed by either Special Agents [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "or Sanders with the Army or Air Force and they are not aware of the telegram sent b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "by Mr. Ripley to Mr. Winchell.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "RECOMMENDATION:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "The foregoing is for your information and any disposition being desirable.",
      "status": "image_matched"
